      • parse

        protected <E> E parse(Node node,
                      java.lang.Class<E> type)
        Parses a given node as the given type of object. Any changes made to the parser during parsing (e.g. defining objects) will be undone before this method returns. One exception applies: any time a domain or problem is parsed, those objects become permanently defined for this parser.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type of the object to construct
        Parameters:
        node - the node to parse
        type - the type of object to construct
        Returns:
        the object
        Throws:
        FormatException - if the node is not properly formatted
